null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf6dc2ea6-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2019—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s3506/d/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 3506(d)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “that amount, $850,000,000 shall be limited to obligations related to fishing vessels and fishery facilities.” for “that amount—” and pars. (1) and (2) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) $850,000,000 shall be limited to obligations related to fishing vessels and fishery facilities; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) $3,000,000,000 shall be limited to obligations related to eligible export vessels.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s3506/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 3506(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subpars. (B) to (K) as (A) to (J), respectively, and struck out former subpar. (A) which read as follows: “if applicable, the country risk for each eligible export vessel financed or to be financed by an obligation;”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/s3522/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, § 3522(b)","children":[],"tail":", repealed "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/s3507/a/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, § 3507(a)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":". See 2006 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/s3522/a/10/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, § 3522(a)(10)(B)","children":[],"tail":", incorporated the substance of the amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/s3507/a/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, § 3507(a)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", into this section by inserting “or Administrator” after “Secretary” wherever appearing. See 2006 Amendment note below and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s18/a"},"text":"section 18(a) of Pub. L. 109–304","children":[],"tail":", set out as a Legislative Purpose and Construction note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/s3507/a/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, § 3507(a)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the amendment of section 1273(h) of the former Appendix to this title from which subsec. (c) of this section was derived, was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/s3522/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, § 3522(b)","children":[],"tail":". See 2008 Amendment note for subsec. (c) and Historical and Revision notes above."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
